10/03/2008
TIRANA, Albania -- Socialist Party (SP) leader Edi Rama said on Sunday (March 9th) that his party is a modern opposition formation that aims to achieve Albania's integration in NATO and the EU. He added that he will not allow anybody to impose their views and opinions on his coalition. As for electoral reform efforts, Rama said his coalition is working with other political parties, but failed to say whether it will co-operate with the ruling Democratic Party. (Shekulli, Shqip - 09/03/08; BalkanWeb, Top-Channel - 08/03/08)
